 to stitch up the tender process so the commercial fishing industry would be monitoring itself?</p><p class="SupAnswer"><strong>Hon JO GOODHEW</strong>: I reject the assertion in the member's question.</p><p class="SupQuestion"><strong>Hon Damien O'Connor</strong>: Does the Minister think New Zealand's international export reputation is at risk when the integrity of the Ministry for Primary Industries and the fishing industry is under question?</p><p class="SupAnswer"><strong>Hon JO GOODHEW</strong>: Quite the contrary. I think what the international industry will see is that we have had an independent inquiry into our fisheries compliance investigations, that we have taken on the chin that in the case of one of them it was flawed, that we have said we have a total commitment to changing the internal processes that have brought this about, and that in fact we are not hiding the fact that there have been mistakes made.</p><p class="QOAEnd"><a name="time_20160922 14:57:06 " ></a><strong> </strong></p></div></body>
